The Fourth Plenary Session of the CCP Central Committee is currently being held in Beijing. On the surface it’s about the “15th Five-Year Plan,” but the real spotlight has fallen on—Chen Jining. Multiple Hong Kong outlets say he may be brought to Beijing to serve as Director of the General Office of the CCP Central Committee, which is the most sensitive power core around Xi Jinping: it manages documents, meetings, and the Central Guard Bureau. If true, it would mean a “quiet blood transfusion of power” is underway in Zhongnanhai. description:
Beijing’s in a panic. As the CCP’s Fourth Plenum opens, power is tearing apart. Rumors say Li Qiang submitted a resignation letter; Xi Jinping slammed the table and barked, “No resignation allowed.” The 82nd Group Army reportedly moved into Beijing on alert; Zhang Youxia and Liu Yuan are suspected of encircling the Jingxi Hotel. The PLA Daily’s front-page “two resolute’s” pledge looks like schizophrenic loyalty—praising Xi while expelling his confidants. This meeting isn’t a meeting—it’s a showdown in Zhongnanhai. description:

Of 205 Central Committee members, 46 are already out of post; the Fourth Plenum is set to become a stage for “rubber-stamping the purge list.” Meanwhile, Prophecy in Tui Bei Tu Diagram 46 resurfaced — “a soldier bearing a bow” — and the name Zhang Youxia once again invites speculation.
